  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Start by pickling your onions, they will be ready by the time the rest of your ingredients are. Finely slice the onion. Add 120ml of water, 120ml apple cider vinegar, 1 ½ tsp sugar, 1 ½ tsp sea salt, and ¼ tsp red pepper flakes to a small saucepan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Soak the sunflower seeds in the lime juice and set aside for 5 mins to absorb. Add 1 chili, salt and paprika and mix. Add a little oil to a pan and fry on medium for a few minutes until crispy but take care not to burn."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "In a blender, add in your yoghurt, coriander, 1 red chilli and the juice of half a lime. Blend until smooth and season with plenty of salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To cook the kebab protein, simply add a little oil to a frying pan and sauté until the sides start to crisp up."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the cucumber and remaining chilli and chop up some coriander for garnishing."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To assemble, warm through your wraps then layer on the yoghurt, the kebab protein and the cucumber. Sprinkle over some sunflower seeds and finish with the pickled onion, sliced chilli, and coriander."
    }
  ],
